C%22%5C%22%3EPeter%20Thiel's%20fellows%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20extended%20more%20than%20%24100%20million%20to%20dozens%20of%20government%20contractors%20scrambling%20for%20cash.%20Founder%20Eva%20Shang%20says%20that's%20about%20twice%20what%20it%20deployed%20in%20the%20three%20years%20since%20launching%20its%20government%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20doubled%20its%20origination%20team%20to%20meet%20demand%2C%20Shang%20said%2C%20and%20closed%20%2440%20million%20from%20new%20investors%20in%20June%20to%20expand%20the%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegalist%20is%20best%20known%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpower-players-litigation-funding-finance-burford-parabellum-legal-law-firms-2021-5%3Fr%3Dlitigation-teaser%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elitigation%20funder%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20uses%20algorithms%20to%20scan%20court%20dockets%2C%20backs%20cases%20it%20thinks%20are%20likely%20to%20win%2C%20and%20takes%20a%20cut%20of%20any%20settlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20at%20the%20urging%20of%20an%20investor%20tied%20to%20a%20university%20endowment%2C%20it%20branched%20into%20%26quot%3Bgovernment%20receivables%2C%26quot%3B%20providing%20upfront%20cash%20to%20contractors%20for%20goods%20or%20services%20they've%20already%20delivered%20but%20haven't%20yet%20been%20paid%20for.%20Legalist%20takes%20its%20cut%20when%20the%20government%20eventually%20settles%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20sideline%20became%20a%20profit%20center%20under%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20as%20contract%20terminations%2C%20stop-work%20orders%2C%20and%20spending%20freezes%20choked%20off%20cash%20for%20contractors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoge.gov%2Fsavings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDOGE%20says%3C%2Fa%3E%20it's%20canceled%20about%20%2458%20billion%20in%20contracts%2C%20while%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2025%2F08%2F12%2Ftrump-doge-contract-claims-savings-inflation-00498178%3Fnid%3D0000018f-3124-de07-a98f-3be4d1400000%26nname%3Dpolitico-toplines%26nrid%3D3c33336c-185c-4448-ab2e-847ddc08b719%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPolitico%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20number%20was%20inflated%20by%20%26quot%3Baccounting%20tricks%26quot%3B%20and%20claims%20that%20couldn't%20be%20verified.%20The%20White%20House%20defended%20DOGE's%20math%2C%20but%20Politico%20said%20it%20could%20identify%20%241.4%20billion%20in%20money%20that%20was%20actually%20clawed%20back%20from%20contractors%20through%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20rules%20let%20contractors%20recover%20money%20when%20policy%20shifts%20derail%20their%20work%20%E2%80%94%20either%20by%20adjusting%20the%20contract%20if%20the%20pause%20drove%20up%20costs%2C%20or%20by%20settling%20up%20if%20the%20job%20is%20canceled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20those%20contractors%20have%20bills%20to%20pay%2C%20creating%20a%20billion-dollar%20opportunity%20for%20private%20credit%20lenders%20like%20Legalist%20and%20its%20largely%20regional%20competitors.%20(Shang%20says%20the%20company%20targets%20an%20interest%20rate%20of%20at%20least%2012%25%2C%20above%20the%20cost%20of%20capital%20at%20traditional%20banks.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegalist%20now%20has%20over%2050%20borrowers.%20One%20is%20a%20privately%20held%20international%20developer%20that%20incurred%20nearly%20%24200%20million%20in%20debt%20for%20services%20already%20rendered%20after%20Trump's%20sweeping%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-elon-musk-usaid-funding-freeze-layoffs-furloughs-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efreeze%20on%20foreign%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%20payments.%20Another%20is%20a%20manufacturer%20of%20aerospace%20engine%20parts%20that%20contracts%20with%20both%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20and%20private-sector%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn