gure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EYear%201947%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENothing%20in%20the%20air%20suggested%20the%20day%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20life-changing%20one%20for%20Amolak%20Singh%20Bhatia.%20He%20woke%20up.%20Proceeded%20with%20his%20routine.%20Did%20not%20dwell%20too%20much%20on%20the%20rumours%20that%20India%20was%20going%20to%20be%20divided.%C2%A0Even%20if%20that%20happened%2C%20his%20village%2C%20Dheerkay%20Kalan%20(present-day%20Pakistan)%2C%20was%20too%20small%20to%20be%20affected%2C%20he%20believed.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Sahiba%20Kaur%20Chhabra%2C%20part%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%201947%20Partition%20Archive%3C%2Fem%3E%20team%2C%20retells%20the%20story%20of%20her%20grandfather%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F316761%2Fhistory-and-origin-of-tandoor-from-indus-valley-to-moti-mahal-kundal-lal-gujral%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emigration%20to%20India%20during%20Partition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20shares%20how%20the%20magnanimity%20of%20the%20event%20took%20years%20to%20settle%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20truck%20came%20to%20take%20the%20family%20to%20the%20station%20from%20where%20they%20would%20go%20to%20Amritsar%2C%20my%20great-grandfather%20quickly%20scribbled%20an%20%3Cem%3Eamanat%20nama%3C%2Fem%3E%20(trust%20document)%20bequeathing%20all%20their%20assets%20to%20their%20Muslim%20neighbours%20until%20the%20time%20they%20got%20back%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sahiba%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20be%20back%2C%E2%80%9D%20was%20the%20promise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFate%20knew%20better.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20while%20Amolak%E2%80%99s%20memories%20of%20Partition%20are%20coloured%20with%20fear%2C%20confusion%2C%20and%20grief%2C%20there%20are%20two%20stories%20he%20always%20tells%20Sahiba%2C%20to%20underscore%20how%2C%20even%20in%20the%20darkest%20of%20times%2C%20humanity%20breathed%20hope.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESahiba%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9COn%20the%20train%20journey%20to%20Amritsar%2C%20there%20was%20a%20rumour%20that%20the%20railway%20station%20water%20had%20been%20poisoned%20so%20that%20anyone%20who%20drank%20the%20water%20would%20die.%20A%20military%20personnel%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Muslim%2C%20who%20was%20assigned%20the%20duty%20of%20taking%20this%20cohort%20of%20people%20to%20the%20Indian%20side%20of%20the%20border%20%E2%80%94%20volunteered%20to%20drink%20the%20water%20and%20test%20it.%20%E2%80%98Even%20if%20it%20is%20poisoned%2C%20I%20will%20die.%20You%20will%20all%20be%20safe%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20told%20the%20people%20on%20the%20train.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20stories%20underscore%20an%20irony.%20While%20religion%20became%20the%20pretext%20of%20Partition%2C%20it%20also%20became%20the%20reason%20for%20hope.%20And%2C%20in%20these%20conversations%2C%20I%20found%20the%20answer%20to%20my%20question.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20scars%20ever%20heal%3F%20Does%20the%20pain%20ever%20lessen%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20lives%20on.%20In%20the%20changed%20food%20habits%20of%20the%20people%20who%20crossed%20the%20border%2C%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98we%E2%80%99ll%20be%20back%E2%80%99s%20that%20were%20never%20fulfilled%2C%20in%20the%20crinkle%20of%20their%20eyes%20every%20time%20they%20think%20of%20how%20they%20shut%20their%20home%20doors%20for%20one%20last%20time%20%E2%80%94%20knowing%20they%E2%80%99d%20never%20return.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20wound%20is%20there.%20The%20bleeding%20has%20stopped.%20But%20the%20scar%20might%20never%20fade.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20again%2C%20it%20depends%20on%20how%20you%20see%20scars.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20can%20either%20be%20reminders%20of%20hurt.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOr%20reminders%20of%20survival.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755261000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2Fbah